This repository contains three kinds of material, licensed separately:

1. CODE (everything under scripts/, plus pyproject.toml and other build
   tooling): MIT License, reproduced below.

2. TEXT (text/ and the chapter text inside the ebook): The Federalist
   Papers (1787-1788) are in the public domain. The transcription used
   here comes from The Avalon Project at Yale Law School
   (https://avalon.law.yale.edu/subject_menus/fed.asp).

3. AUDIO (audio/, captions/, and the narration embedded in the ebook):
   The narration was recorded and published by VonClegg Classics
   (https://www.youtube.com/@voncleggclassics5928), who retains all
   rights to it. It is included here with attribution. The ebook
   (build/the-federalist-papers.epub) is free for anyone to use, copy,
   and share, but because the narration belongs to VonClegg Classics it
   MUST NOT be sold or otherwise monetized, and any redistribution must
   keep this credit to VonClegg Classics.

